<TITLE> Tornado strikes 2 Jamalpur Upazila </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jamalpur, Sept 5 (bdnews24.com)  A tornado swept through several villages of Melandah and Madarganj Upazila in Jamalpur in the early hours of Friday, leaving at least 50 people injured, government officials said. The affected villages are Telipara, Rekhir Para, Chinasukhpara, Gumrapara and Paharipatal of Melandah Upazila and Baistepara of Madarganj Upazila. Melandah Upazila Nirbahi Officer Masud Alam Chowdhury said 120 families had been affected by the tornado. Anna Begum of Rekhir Para village said she and her one-and-a-half-years old baby boy were trapped under their tin-shed roof. Her neighbours later rescued them. "Heavy wind swept away everything from the village," Anna said. Fulkocha Union Parishad chairman Manjurul Islam said he had visited five villages where at least 30 people were injured. Madarganj Upazila Nirbahi Officer Md Nuruzzaman said 80 families of the Upazila were affected and 20 people injured. bdnews
